div.p: Ratio: A comparison of two numbers or quantities with the same units.
Rate: A comparison of two quantities with different units (e.g., miles per hour).
Unit Rate: A rate where the second quantity is one unit (e.g., $20/hour).

ul.li: Ratio of apples to oranges: 5:3 or 5/3.
Rate: 40 miles per hour (40 miles/1 hour).
If a car travels 120 miles in 3 hours, what is its unit rate?
A fruit stand sells 7 apples for every 4 oranges. What is the ratio of apples to oranges?
Ratios compare quantities with the same units.
Rates compare quantities with different units.
